1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE
RESOLUTION 1048 By: Pae
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 A Resolution designating April 15 as the Purple Up!
For Military Kids Day in Oklahoma; and thanking
8 military families.
9
10
11 WHEREAS, April is recognized worldwide as the Month of the
12 Military Child, with special recognition on April 15 as Purple Up!
13 For Military Kids Day; and
14 WHEREAS, the Month of the Military Child was established in 1986
15 by former United States Secretary of Defense Caspar Weinberger to
16 honor the sacrifices made by military families and to acknowledge
17 the vital role military children play within the armed forces
18 community; and
19 WHEREAS, military children face unique challenges as a result of
20 their parents' incredible service, including frequent relocations,
21 long separations, and multiple deployments to combat zones, all
22 while enduring the uncertainty of their parents' safe return; and
23
24
Req. No. 17174 Page 1

1 WHEREAS, these children exemplify resilience, courage, and
2 strength, navigating the hardships of military life with admirable
3 perseverance and adaptability; and
4 WHEREAS, the tradition of wearing purple, known as the "purple
5 suit", symbolizes unity across all branches of the military —
6 combining Air Force blue, Army green, Navy blue, Marine red, and
7 Coast Guard blue to represent a shared commitment to service and
8 sacrifice; and
9 WHEREAS, on April 15, wearing purple serves as a visible tribute
10 to military children, celebrating their important contributions.
11 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
12 OF THE 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
13 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives designates April 15
14 as Purple Up! For Military Kids Day in Oklahoma.
15 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives expresses gratitude
16 to military families and their children for their sacrifice and
17 dedication to our state and nation.
